HEADWORD: Ogygian
<hw>O*gyg"i*an</hw> <pr>(⟦osl⟧*j⟦icr⟧j"⟦icr⟧*⟦ait⟧n)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<ety>[L. <ets>Ogygius</ets>, Gr. <grk>'Ogy`gios</grk>.]</ety> <def>Of or
pertaining to <persfn>Ogyges</persfn>, a mythical king of ancient
Attica, or to a great deluge in Attica in his days; hence, primeval; of
obscure antiquity.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

